loud.name: Guitar Amp Loud Tube Amplifier Crate Tube amp
loud.description: Like new condition- still in the box and styrofoam!Huge amount of sound for the price! Good for gigging musician, home or studio.The new V50-112 two-channel combo loudly announces the new generation of Crates all-tube amplifiers. With dual 6L6 fixed biased output tubes, this bad refrigerator produces the sort of sparkling cleans and warm, thick overdrive that can only come from tubes pushed to their limit. It pumps 50 watts through a single 12 speaker, creating a muscular low end perfect for club gigs and recording sessions. Presence control, spring reverb and foot-switchable boost make sure you can dial in your custom tone from anywhere. Lesser amps will blow their fuses in fear when they see you plugging into a V50-112.Features & details50 Watts RMS1 x 12-inch speakerTwo channels2 x 6L6 output tubes, fixed biasFootswitchable Boost$349 or best offerKeyword Guit guitar guitar amplifiers amp fender Gibson Peavey Marshall Mesa boogie Ludwig Gretsch strat speaker

loud.name: Roland TD-9 Electronic Drum Set
loud.description: Roland TD-9 V-Drums with an extra floor tom. Includes headphones, throne and bass drum pedal.  Works perfectly.  I am also including a headphone amplifier as the TD-9 is known for being a little bit light on volume.  With the amp it will go as loud as you would like.

famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most solid-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The Famous FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Subtle striping at the soundhole is nice touch. Low action and great intonation, it's got a classic ukulele sound. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail.Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: Ashdown Rootmaster 420W Solid State 2x10 Bass Combo,w/ Sub Harmonics
famous.description: Only ever been played a few times,(inside/practice only, never used for a live gig which was the original intention, so it is basically unused). I am not mobile with a car, so only reach out if you are willing to drive over/commute to Hayes Valley and pick it up, serious inquiries only please. Rootmaster heads, combos and cabinets draw on all of our experience working with some of the biggest bands in the world to deliver workhorse reliability, creative tone-shaping, comprehensive recording and performing facilities plus the sonic slam you need to underpin your band's performances night after night - all at a price that won't break the bank.Powered by 420W digital amp, it is ideal for players who favors a tight, defined sound, delivering it's power via a pair of 10 custom, supplemented by a high-frequency piezo for increased top end bite and articulation.Simple, powerful EQIt all starts with an ultra-low-noise instrument input where the accompanying Input Level control helps you perfectly match the output of your bass. Five-band rotary tone controls act with surgical precision to provide total control over your sound, while a Shape switch instantly dials you in to a classic Ashdown tone setting, straight from the world-famous ABM.One-knob CompressionInstantly adding warmth and body to your tone, this simple to use, great sounding compressor delivers a powerful, even sound to make sure your bass will fill out any mix.Footswitchable variable overdriveWith footswitchable flexibility, our tube-emulated overdrive can take your core bass sound and push it into warm overdrive through to distorted filth whenever you need to add extra grind and girth to your tone.Kick it downBringing extra depth and definition to your bass parts, the Sub-Harmonic Generator lets you dial in a sub-octave and kick it in via footswitch whenever you need the extra depth for those super-heavy Godzilla moments.Totally connectedIf you want to use your favorite pedals or multi-effects, you'll find send and return sockets on the back panel, along with a DI output for direct injection into the PA mixer or recording console and a Line Input (with front panel level control) so you can jam along with a backing track in rehearsal.Create the perfect rig2 x 10, 4 x 10 and 2 x 12 cabs all feature custom-designed Ashdown bass drivers plus a high-frequency horn for additional top-end bite. A 1 x 15 completes the range with all cabinets featuring ultra-cool retro cloth grilles, road-ready tolex covering and tough metal protective corners.

famous.name: 1880's Isidor Lot Wood Flute
famous.description: This flute was made by Isidor Lot, perhaps the nephew of the Famous flutemaker Louis Lotin the 1880's. It is openhole, inline G, C foot and was restored by Daniel Deitch in San Francisco.The sound is warm and sweet and has nothing to do with the volume of the 21st century.It comes in the original case.
